    "gauge_law_verbatim": "SINGLE-EDGE GAUGE (Stage C, declared DBP frame). The gauge is the border shear acting on the jet (g, H): g is UNCHANGED; H -> H + t*(g e_i^T + e_i g^T), i.e. H[a][c] += t*(g[a]*[c==i] + [a==i]*g[c]) for the basis direction e_i (i in {1,2,3}), t in Q. Because the tangent-plane projector P = I - g g^T/q annihilates the gradient (P g = 0, g^T P = 0), the gauge generator satisfies P (g e_i^T + e_i g^T) P = 0, so the tangent shape operator P H P is EXACTLY unchanged: every shape invariant sigma_r is preserved (here, n=3 -> 2-dim tangent plane -> sigma_1 = tr(PHP)/|g| and sigma_2 = det = K_G). q = g^T g is invariant (g is unchanged). The channel decomposition C = (kappa_c, kappa_s, kappa_int) MOVES within the fiber but its sum is fixed: delta C in ker Sigma (Sigma: Q^3 -> Q, Sigma(a,b,c)=a+b+c), i.e. delta K_G = 0. The single-edge law (a symbolic identity over Q in (t, g, H)) is delta kappa_c(t e_i) = 4 t (prod g) H_jk / q^2, where {j,k} is the index pair complementary to i (equivalently delta Delta_c = -4 t (prod g) H_jk; Delta_c uses q^2). At the keystone F8 (g=(3,1,2), H=[[2,1,0],[1,0,0],[0,0,2]], q=14, prod g = 6, q^2 = 196): e1 PINS (complement {2,3}, H_23=0 => delta kappa_c = 0), e2 PINS (complement {1,3}, H_13=0 => delta kappa_c = 0), e3 MOVES (complement {1,2}, H_12=1 => delta kappa_c = 4*6*1/196 = 24/196 = 6/49 per unit t).",
