    "probe_source_verbatim": "\"\"\"c001 `three_channel_kg` \u2014 the PROBE (Path A, `role=probe`).\n\nThe monomial channel read-off. From the bordered Hessian\n\n        H_b = [[ 0 , g\u1d40 ],\n               [ g ,  H ]]      (4\u00d74, H symmetric 3\u00d73, q = g\u1d40g \u2260 0)\n\nwe form det(H_b) as an exact polynomial in (g, H) and partition it into the\nexhaustive, disjoint monomial classes pinned in `manifest_v1.json` \u2192\n`semantics_pinned` and `results/three_channel_kg/SCHEMA.md`:\n\n  * \u0394_c \u2014 monomials carrying an OFF-DIAGONAL H-entry only (coupling),\n  * \u0394_s \u2014 monomials carrying a DIAGONAL H-entry only (self),\n  * \u0394_m \u2014 MIXED monomials (one diagonal \u00d7 one off-diagonal),\n\nwith  det(H_b) == \u0394_c + \u0394_s + \u0394_m  (closure identity #5). Then\n\n        \u03ba_X = \u2212\u0394_X / q\u00b2        and        K_G = \u03ba_c + \u03ba_s + \u03ba_int.\n\n(\u03ba_int is the channel read off from the mixed partition \u0394_m.)\n\nTHE LINE (covenant): this is the HYPOTHESIS path. The probe NEVER imports the\nreferee \u2014 truth (Path B total, Path B\u2032 channels, Path C oracle) is computed on\nan independent code path this module never sees. Exact \u211a ONLY: every operand\nand result is a `fractions.Fraction`; there is no float, no radical, and no\ntolerance anywhere below. The singular stratum (a VANISHING gradient: q=0,\nthe cone-apex / critical point, equivalently every g\u1d62=0) is REFUSED with a\ntyped exception, never returned as 0 / NaN / a placeholder (refuse-not-lie).\nA regular jet that merely has one zero gradient component (q\u22600) is NOT\nsingular and computes normally \u2014 see the frozen fixture F6.\n\nThe det(H_b) used here is the read-off's OWN exact-\u211a expansion of the\nbordered determinant (cofactor expansion along the border, in `Fraction`); it\nis hypothesis input on Path A, independently re-derived by the referee on\nPath B before any row is graded \u2014 the probe does not consult that path.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom fractions import Fraction\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Sequence, Tuple\n\nPROBE_ID = \"three_channel_kg_probe_A_v1\"\nROLE = \"probe\"\n\n\nclass ThreeChannelRefusal(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Typed refusal on a singular stratum (refuse-not-lie). `kind` is one of\n    the `schema.SINGULAR_STRATA` labels.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, kind: str) -> None:\n        super().__init__(kind)\n        self.kind = kind\n\n\nVec3 = Sequence[Fraction]\nMat3 = Sequence[Sequence[Fraction]]\n\n\n# --------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# exact-Q guards\n# --------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef _as_fraction(x: object, where: str) -> Fraction:\n    \"\"\"Admit only exact rationals onto the probe path. A float or any\n    non-exact type is a \u221aq-leak at the door and is refused as a type error \u2014\n    never silently coerced.\"\"\"\n    if isinstance(x, Fraction):\n        return x\n    if isinstance(x, int) and not isinstance(x, bool):\n        return Fraction(x)\n    raise TypeError(\n        f\"{where}: probe path is exact \u211a only; got \"\n        f\"{type(x).__name__} ({x!r}) \u2014 no float/radical admitted\")\n\n\ndef _coerce_jet(g: Vec3, H: Mat3) -> Tuple[List[Fraction], List[List[Fraction]]]:\n    if len(g) != 3:\n        raise ValueError(f\"g must have length 3, got {len(g)}\")\n    if len(H) != 3 or any(len(row) != 3 for row in H):\n        raise ValueError(\"H must be 3x3\")\n    gg = [_as_fraction(g[i], f\"g[{i}]\") for i in range(3)]\n    HH = [[_as_fraction(H[i][j], f\"H[{i}][{j}]\") for j in range(3)]\n          for i in range(3)]\n    # H is the Hessian: symmetric. Enforce it (an asymmetric H would make the\n    # off/diagonal monomial classes ill-defined).\n    for i in range(3):\n        for j in range(i + 1, 3):\n            if HH[i][j] != HH[j][i]:\n                raise ValueError(\n                    f\"H not symmetric at ({i},{j}): \"\n                    f\"{HH[i][j]} != {HH[j][i]}\")\n    return gg, HH\n\n\n# --------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# q = g^T g, with the singular-stratum refusals (refuse-not-lie)\n# --------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef q_of(g: Vec3) -> Fraction:\n    \"\"\"q = g\u1d40g in exact \u211a. Refuses the singular stratum (refuse-not-lie):\n    when the gradient VANISHES (q=0) there is no regular level surface \u2014 the\n    cone-apex / critical point \u2014 and the read-off is a TYPED `q_zero` refusal,\n    never 0 / NaN / a placeholder.\n\n    A single zero gradient COMPONENT (some g\u1d62=0 with q\u22600) is NOT singular: it\n    is a regular rational jet in the supplied frame (e.g. the frozen fixture\n    F6, sphere at (3/5,4/5,0) with g=(6/5,8/5,0), q=4, K_G=1). The spec's\n    `g\u1d62=0` singular stratum is the genuine degeneracy where the gradient drops\n    rank to zero (q=0 \u27fa every g\u1d62=0 over \u211d), reported as `g_i_zero`; it does\n    NOT include regular points that merely lie on a coordinate hyperplane.\n    Over-refusing F6 would contradict the freeze, so the gate is strictly q=0.\n    \"\"\"\n    gg = [_as_fraction(g[i], f\"g[{i}]\") for i in range(3)]\n    q = gg[0] * gg[0] + gg[1] * gg[1] + gg[2] * gg[2]\n    if q == 0:\n        # gradient vanishes: cone apex / critical point. Over \u211d this is\n        # exactly \"every g\u1d62=0\", so name both the apex and the g\u1d62=0 stratum.\n        kind = \"g_i_zero\" if all(gi == 0 for gi in gg) else \"q_zero\"\n        raise ThreeChannelRefusal(kind)\n    return q\n\n\n# --------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# the bordered-Hessian determinant, partitioned by monomial class (Path A)\n# --------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef partition(g: Vec3, H: Mat3\n              ) -> Dict[str, Fraction]:\n    \"\"\"Return {'Delta_c','Delta_s','Delta_m','det_hb'} \u2014 the exact-\u211a\n    monomial partition of det(H_b).\n\n    det(H_b) for H_b = [[0, g\u1d40],[g, H]] expands (exactly, in \u211a) to the twelve\n    additive terms\n\n        det = g1\u00b2(h23\u00b2 \u2212 h22\u00b7h33)            \u2190 s: \u2212g1\u00b2h22h33, c: +g1\u00b2h23\u00b2\n            + g2\u00b2(h13\u00b2 \u2212 h11\u00b7h33)            \u2190 s: \u2212g2\u00b2h11h33, c: +g2\u00b2h13\u00b2\n            + g3\u00b2(h12\u00b2 \u2212 h11\u00b7h22)            \u2190 s: \u2212g3\u00b2h11h22, c: +g3\u00b2h12\u00b2\n            + 2g1g2(h12\u00b7h33 \u2212 h13\u00b7h23)       \u2190 m: +2g1g2h12h33, c: \u22122g1g2h13h23\n            + 2g1g3(h13\u00b7h22 \u2212 h12\u00b7h23)       \u2190 m: +2g1g3h13h22, c: \u22122g1g3h12h23\n            + 2g2g3(h11\u00b7h23 \u2212 h12\u00b7h13)       \u2190 m: +2g2g3h11h23, c: \u22122g2g3h12h13\n\n    classified by the H-entries each monomial carries:\n      diagonal-only  (h11,h22,h33)               -> \u0394_s,\n      off-diagonal-only (h12,h13,h23)            -> \u0394_c,\n      one diagonal \u00d7 one off-diagonal            -> \u0394_m.\n    The bordered determinant has no H-free term, so the three classes are\n    exhaustive and disjoint and \u0394_c+\u0394_s+\u0394_m == det(H_b) identically.\n    \"\"\"\n    gg, HH = _coerce_jet(g, H)\n    g1, g2, g3 = gg\n    h11, h12, h13 = HH[0][0], HH[0][1], HH[0][2]\n    h22, h23, h33 = HH[1][1], HH[1][2], HH[2][2]\n\n    # \u0394_c \u2014 off-diagonal-H monomials only\n    delta_c = (g1 * g1 * h23 * h23\n               - 2 * g1 * g2 * h13 * h23\n               - 2 * g1 * g3 * h12 * h23\n               + g2 * g2 * h13 * h13\n               - 2 * g2 * g3 * h12 * h13\n               + g3 * g3 * h12 * h12)\n\n    # \u0394_s \u2014 diagonal-H monomials only\n    delta_s = (- g1 * g1 * h22 * h33\n               - g2 * g2 * h11 * h33\n               - g3 * g3 * h11 * h22)\n\n    # \u0394_m \u2014 mixed monomials (one diagonal \u00d7 one off-diagonal)\n    delta_m = (2 * g1 * g2 * h12 * h33\n               + 2 * g1 * g3 * h13 * h22\n               + 2 * g2 * g3 * h11 * h23)\n\n    det_hb = _det_bordered(gg, HH)\n\n    # closure identity #5, asserted on the probe's own arithmetic: the\n    # partition must reconstruct the cofactor-expanded determinant exactly.\n    # (This is an internal self-consistency guard on Path A only \u2014 NOT the\n    # referee's Path-B determinant, which the probe never imports.)\n    if delta_c + delta_s + delta_m != det_hb:\n        raise AssertionError(\n            \"Path-A partition broke det(H_b)=\u0394_c+\u0394_s+\u0394_m: \"\n            f\"{delta_c}+{delta_s}+{delta_m} != {det_hb}\")\n\n    return {\"Delta_c\": delta_c, \"Delta_s\": delta_s,\n            \"Delta_m\": delta_m, \"det_hb\": det_hb}\n\n\ndef _det_bordered(g: List[Fraction], H: List[List[Fraction]]) -> Fraction:\n    \"\"\"det of the 4\u00d74 bordered Hessian [[0, g\u1d40],[g, H]], by cofactor\n    expansion along the first (border) row, in exact \u211a. Independent of the\n    monomial split above \u2014 it is the read-off's own determinant so the\n    closure-#5 guard is meaningful.\"\"\"\n    hb = [[Fraction(0), g[0], g[1], g[2]],\n          [g[0], H[0][0], H[0][1], H[0][2]],\n          [g[1], H[1][0], H[1][1], H[1][2]],\n          [g[2], H[2][0], H[2][1], H[2][2]]]\n    return _det4(hb)\n\n\ndef _det4(m: List[List[Fraction]]) -> Fraction:\n    \"\"\"Exact 4\u00d74 determinant via Laplace expansion along row 0 (3\u00d73 minors by\n    the rule of Sarrus). Pure Fraction; no pivoting/division, so nothing can\n    go non-exact.\"\"\"\n    acc = Fraction(0)\n    sign = Fraction(1)\n    for c in range(4):\n        if m[0][c] != 0:\n            minor = [[m[r][cc] for cc in range(4) if cc != c]\n                     for r in range(1, 4)]\n            acc += sign * m[0][c] * _det3(minor)\n        sign = -sign\n    return acc\n\n\ndef _det3(m: List[List[Fraction]]) -> Fraction:\n    return (m[0][0] * (m[1][1] * m[2][2] - m[1][2] * m[2][1])\n            - m[0][1] * (m[1][0] * m[2][2] - m[1][2] * m[2][0])\n            + m[0][2] * (m[1][0] * m[2][1] - m[1][1] * m[2][0]))\n\n\n# --------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# the channel read-off: kappa_X = -Delta_X / q^2, K_G = kappa_c+kappa_s+kappa_int\n# --------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef read_off(g: Vec3, H: Mat3) -> Dict[str, Fraction]:\n    \"\"\"Path A. Returns the exact-\u211a dict\n\n        {'K_G','kappa_c','kappa_s','kappa_int',\n         'q','Delta_c','Delta_s','Delta_m','det_hb'}\n\n    Raises `ThreeChannelRefusal` on a singular stratum (q=0 / g\u1d62=0). No\n    float, radical, or tolerance is used; the bordered determinant is \u221aq-free\n    (q enters only as q\u00b2, never \u221aq).\"\"\"\n    q = q_of(g)                      # refuses g\u1d62=0 / q=0\n    q2 = q * q\n    part = partition(g, H)\n    kappa_c = -part[\"Delta_c\"] / q2\n    kappa_s = -part[\"Delta_s\"] / q2\n    kappa_int = -part[\"Delta_m\"] / q2\n    K_G = kappa_c + kappa_s + kappa_int\n    return {\"K_G\": K_G, \"kappa_c\": kappa_c, \"kappa_s\": kappa_s,\n            \"kappa_int\": kappa_int, \"q\": q,\n            \"Delta_c\": part[\"Delta_c\"], \"Delta_s\": part[\"Delta_s\"],\n            \"Delta_m\": part[\"Delta_m\"], \"det_hb\": part[\"det_hb\"]}\n\n\ndef channels(g: Vec3, H: Mat3\n             ) -> Tuple[Fraction, Fraction, Fraction, Fraction]:\n    \"\"\"Convenience: the graded tuple (K_G, \u03ba_c, \u03ba_s, \u03ba_int) in exact \u211a.\"\"\"\n    r = read_off(g, H)\n    return r[\"K_G\"], r[\"kappa_c\"], r[\"kappa_s\"], r[\"kappa_int\"]\n\n\n__all__ = [\n    \"PROBE_ID\", \"ROLE\", \"ThreeChannelRefusal\",\n    \"q_of\", \"partition\", \"read_off\", \"channels\",\n]\n",
